################# Tomcat8 ####################

-> Apache tomcat is a open source web server and servlet container.
-> It is developed by the apache software foundation is also know as ASF.
-> Tomcat implements Java Servlet(JSP) and Javaserver pages specification from Sun Micro systems.
-> It provides a "Pure Java " web server environment.
-> It includes tools for configuartion and management.
-> It can be configured directly by editing XML configuration files.
-> Tomcate written in Java language.
-> It is cross-platform software works on various operating systems.


-> Tomcat8 is application webserver
-> Deploy to container = jenkins plugin
-> To run jar file in linux = #java -jar load.jar  


-> Install tomcate8: https://linode.com/docs/development/frameworks/apache-tomcat-on-ubuntu-16-04/

-> #cd /var/lib/tomcat8/conf/tomcat-users.xml              
              <role rolename="manager-gui"/>
              <role rolename="manager-script"/>
              <role rolename="manager-jmx"/>
              <role rolename="manager-status"/>
              <user username="username" password="******" roles="manager-script,manager-gui,manager-jmx,manager-status"/>
</tomcat-users>
